name: American Flag - Tank
description:
The national flag of the United States of America, often referred to as the American flag, consists of thirteen equal alternating horizontal stripes bearing fifty small five-pointed stars arranged in nine offset horizontal rows of six stars (top and bottom) alternating with rows of five stars. The 50 stars on the flag represent the 50 states of the United States of America and the 13 stripes represent the thirteen British colonies that declared independence from the Kingdom of Great Britain. Nicknames for the flag include the "Stars and Stripes", "Old Glory", and "The Star-Spangled Banner" - FREE SHIPPING CLICK PICTURES TO ENLARGE Size Chart Color Chart Design: 9"W x 14"H
